{
  "primary_issue": "SQL injection vulnerability in UserDao2 methods (selectAll, updateUser) due to unsanitized user input concatenated into SQL queries.",
  "evidence": "The code directly passes user-controlled parameters (e.g., id, name, pass) to userDao.updateUser(userBean) and userDao.selectAll() without any validation or parameterization. The UserDao2 implementation likely constructs SQL statements using string concatenation, allowing an attacker to inject malicious SQL.",
  "fix_summary": "Use parameterized queries (PreparedStatement) in UserDao2 for all database operations. Validate and sanitize all user inputs before use. Consider using an ORM framework like Hibernate or JPA to avoid raw SQL."
}
